Bucklers and Votive Tables pro Salute Principis, and other
Occasions, are very frequent in Reverses; a Wheel is the Character
of some famous Way made or repaired by the Emperor;


as in a Reverse of Trajan. In short, the Zodiac describ'd
in all its Figures with the Moon in Center, was
Emblem of the universal Happiness of a Princes Government;
such as we meet in a Reverse of Alexander Severus;
and Augustus was fortunate under Capricornus.

alluding to the Union of the two Houses of York and Lancaster;
represented by the Red and White Rose, on which Iohn Owen
                   bestows a Witty Epigram. Lib. 3.

a Hand from Heaven holding a Sword pointing up to a
Crown, with that Worthy Saying of the Emperour Trajan,
delivering a Sword to the Pretor;

Another represents him at length, walking with a Sword
thrust through his Body, and coming out at his Shoulder;
Head and Neck bending down as broken.

